11:21 AM Defendant Jordan Anthony Haskins in court.  Attorney Adam C Benson in court for Jordan Anthony Haskins.  Attorney Kevin Thomas Schmidt in court for State of Wisconsin. Case is on for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Agreement is recited by Court- def pleading G to both charges, DJOC on 1 of the counts; 2 yrs probatoin recommendation.  DJOC and PLQ filed with judge in court.  Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Court reviews Def's constitutional rights.  Def understands that def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for pleas. Def enters a plea of Guilty to both charges.  Court finds def is making pleas knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds a factual basis to accept the pleas.  Court finds defendant guilty of Counts 1 and 2 and orders a JOC on Count 2.  DA asks Court to accept agreement.  Defense attorney asks Court to accept agreement.  Def does not make statement to the Court.  Court adopts the DJOC agreement on Count 1, judgment is deferred for 3 years.  
On Count 2, Court orders: 2 yrs probation, withheld sentence 
Domestic violence education group through RJ, must be signed up by 10/15/2022 and complete the program by 1/31/2023.  The defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. No use or possession of any illegal drugs, paraphernalia, or controlled substances without a valid prescription. No contact with the victim, their family members, or residences.  The defendant shall complete all programming required by the Department of Corrections. $543 court costs- to be taken from bond.  Remaining to be held.  
Appeal rights provided.  DNA to be provided to the Sheriff before leaving the building.
